headline.main: HULL AND HALIFAX STUDY FAR EAST; Briton Interrupts His Visit to Philadelphia for Talk at State Department

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Nov. 29 -- Viscount Halifax, the British Ambassador, and Secretary of State Cordell Hull conferred for nearly an hour this morning on the Pacific crisis under circumstances that suggested that it was more than a routine meeting.
